    <stitle>3300 HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - ADJUSTMENTS - HOOD STOP ADJUSTMENT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="1">
        <title>HOOD STOP ADJUSTMENT</title>
        <para>Hood height adjustment at the cowl and rear edge of hood is adjusted by moving the hood stop either up or
            down.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0901081" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901081.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 90. Hood Stop (Driver Side Shown)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. HOOD STOP BUSHING</callout1>
                <callout1>2. COWL ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>3. THREE MOUNTING BOLTS AND LOCK WASHERS</callout1>
                <callout1>4. HOOD STOP BRACKET</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Unlatch hood and tilt hood forward.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To adjust hood in either direction, loosen the three bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0901081">Figure 90, Item 3</hotlnk>) located at the hood stop bracket.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the bracket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0901081">Figure 90, Item 4</hotlnk>) upward or down to set desired height.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lower the hood and rest hood on hood stop bushings. Check rear edge alignment with cowl.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Raise the hood and retighten the bolts to secure the hood stop at the desired location.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The same procedure should be applied to adjust the opposite side of hood.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten to 147 to 181 LBF-FT (200 to 245 Nm).</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
